Overview

Kerala is widely recognized for its strong public health system and progressive social indicators. Its health initiatives align with UN Sustainable Development Goal 3 (Good Health and Well-being), aiming to ensure healthy lives and promote well-being for all ages. Key focus areas include universal health coverage, maternal and child health, and disease prevention and management. Kerala also emphasizes health education, awareness, and equitable access for all citizens, especially vulnerable populations. The state has achieved high life expectancy, low infant and maternal mortality rates, and extensive vaccination coverage. With innovative programs like telemedicine and digital health records, Kerala serves as a model for sustainable health development in India and globally.
